In case it helps, I've found two gimp scripts that might be useful for the tiles.<br><ul><li><a href="http://registry.gimp.org/node/25040" class="postlink">Isometric floor</a> for ground tiles</li><li><a href="http://registry.gimp.org/node/25043" class="postlink">Isometric wall</a>for walls</li> </ul> <br><br>The antialiasing isn't particularly good, but it can probably give you artists a start.<br><br><a href="http://www.techzilo.com/how-to-install-gimp-plugins-scripts-brushes-and-gradients/" class="postlink">Here's how to install them</a> (they are scripts, not plugins)<br><br>(I know; dimetric, not isometric. Yeah.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=710">kikito</a> — Fri Feb 11, 2011 8:33 am</p><hr />
